  "notes": "Proof authority: Lean kernel via the tracked proof-search loop (episode f99a1298), kernel_verified on the first attempt. Distinct proof style (induction) from packets/elementary/functions/geom_series_mul.v1.json (factorization identity); cross-reference both. Statement proved over ℤ rather than ℕ to keep the (r - 1) subtraction honest (no truncation), matching the domain's `bernoulli_inequality`/`two_pow_gt_self` precedent of picking an ordered ring where the natural algebra holds cleanly.",
